The article discusses the importance of passing the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act, which aims to ease the burden on American taxpayers. The $1.5 trillion tax overhaul package has passed both the House of Representatives and the Senate, and now needs to be reconciled before being signed into law by President Trump. The article argues that the tax reform bill will reduce taxes for every income group and will benefit businesses by cutting the corporate tax rate from 35% to 20%, potentially leading to the creation of almost one million new jobs. It also highlights the benefits for the middle class, as the proposed tax code will be simplified. The article concludes by urging legislators to reconcile the bills and allow hard-working American taxpayers to keep more of their earnings.